tip.text: Nice laksa! Recommended if u wanna try laksa. Laksa soup was tasty too. Tried the Sui Gao  noodle soup. The sui gao was firm and tasty. Soup is slightly salty but similar to Hong Kong.
Love this place... Dark Moka... tried the Chocolate Love cake. Nice!
Laksa was good with decent amount of ingredients. Nasi Lemak was nice too but the rice could have been tastier and with a stronger coconut fragrance. The service was great & loved the Pisang Goreng!
Love the pulled pork burger and Rotterdam coffee! The Seabass paella was good too, despite the small portion.
The tentenman was nice, pretty authentic ramen with my favorite Naturo fishcake ! Slightly spicy.
Salmon quiche was nice. Forgot the name of the bread but it was nice too. Nice ambience while waiting for the ferry.
Buffet@€21.90. Has a variety of food but we didn't go for the buffet. Crowded on a Sunday but the cakes were good. Recommend the shrimp one. Many types of Hot Chocolate drinks.
Carbonara pasta was good but preferred it to be saltier. Love the local beer which I forgot the name. Starts with'S'... Good place to drink and chat with friends...
The layout of the place looks like a posh place with nice food. But the signature soup with special beehoon, was pretty normal. The charsiew and custard buns were normal too. Expected much actually.
Duck was good... Good place to chill out. But service was normal only as they were understaffed.
Sweet & Sour pork was good, except that the meat used were more like fatty meat. Toufu with meat was good too. Use Toilet is €0.50...
Food is nice here. Quite authentic Thai food. Follow the advice on the spicy level of the food. It's pretty accurate.
Wifi password is lbuprofeno. Service was good. Duck kroket was special and full of filling. Food was good and great ambience with hospital settings.
Nice ambience with bean bag chairs by the windows. Food was good too. Love the 'Wok' outlets
Best Bitterballen rated. Sauce was wasabi so take note. Even had the chance to try herring fish which was good. Good ambience for drinks and chats...
Vietnamese noodles was tasty with lots of meat in it.
Interesting and cosy place. No menu available and depends on the chef on what's available on that day. Food was okay too.
Pizza was normal but ambience was good. Great place to chill and eat with friends. Service was good too.
Good Indonesian restaurant. Service was good but slow. They even explained the dishes served. Food was good.
Glutinous rice, Hor Fun, Sweet & Sour pork, vegetables were good; Beancurd skin with quail eggs was special.
Tom yum goong soup's portion was small; Phat Thai was good; Pandan leave chicken was normal but pls eat it while it's hot. Service was good.
Ramen was not bad but gyoza was normal. Prefer miso soup based. Special hoegaarden lime flavor beer but 2% alcohol level only...
Good ambience to chill. Interesting toilets too...
Food was good and so is their service too. Free use of toilet but beware of the low ceiling.
Pork belly meat (燒肉) skin was crispy; fried mango & shrimp didn't had mango taste; siew mai was normal; fried dough rice noodle roll. Porridge was normal too.
A place to find designer outlets and spend time shopping! Free use of toilets!
Nice ambience and waffles!
Need to pay 60 Euros for mayo and tomato sauce. Toilet cost 50 Euros...
Big brands small prices... Great place to find good deals!
Rated one of the best bitterballen. Not bad but note that the sauce is wasabi. Nice cozy place facing the sea. Even have herrings for food tasting...
Satay noodles @ €6.30. Interesting flavor. Doesn't have strong satay taste. Little veg in it.
Working shoes @ €40, Blazers at 2 for €100. Nice and affordable stuff!
My fav place! Cheap stuff! Toilet@L2 at €40...
My fav prata place! Bom Prata and Banana Egg Prata!! Woohoo!!!!
Could not find any pork ball noodles. Tried the chicken one. Sufficient pieces of chicken which was tender. Like the soup too. Side dishes were good too.
Salty egg pork chop rice-> Not bad but with 3 pieces of meat only. @ $6.50
New white bee hoon stall. Tried the prawn which comes with lala. Tasty but might be too ex.

venue.name: Ang Mo Kio Central Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Decent food. Ayam penyet was not bad.
Food was normal. There was a lot of filling in the liu sa bao. Chicken banana not bad. The duck with seafood below dish nice. Come early. Crowded after 10am..

venue.name: Red Star Restaurant 红星酒家

tip.text: Salty egg croissant wasn't that fantastic. Croissant was expectedly good but salty egg was normal. Need to heat up longer in order for the lava to flow out. (The white dot is due to flashlight.)
Tried the red velvet waffle. Not that nice as compared to others. Strawberry icecream was refreshing while coffee icecream was normal.
Love the Himalayan Tea Latte!

formattedAddress: #01-04 Big Mac Centre (51 Ang Mo Kio Ave 3)

tip.text: Charcoal waffle tastes bland, coconut icecream quite tasty. Triple C quite normal, berries icecream not bad. Salty egg sauce was normal. The water tap for people to get free drinking water.
Fishball noodles tasted normal, but the fish balls not bad. Additional food like fish cake cost $2. 3 bowls of noodles (fish+ fishballs), 2x fish cakes, 100plus + 2 x herbal tea bottles = $30+.
Sea salt caramel cheesecake was not bad. Tried the lemon cake but it was sweet. Carbonara pasta was good. Crab meat aglio olio was good too. Good ambience.
Nice ambience but limited parking. Beside airport runway. Tom yum soup mookata was nice n suitable for pple who can take little spice. Mango salad n ice tea were good. Yuzu smoothie was refreshing.
Hokkien noodles was still good after so many years.
Penang curry mee was normal, not much ingredients. The chili paste is important; Without it, the noodles becomes tasteless. 2 pieces of wu xiang cost more than $3.
Japchae was tasty. Pancake was crispy. 3 sauces to choose for Topokki but the manager recommended spicy. It was still pretty spicy even after we have requested for less spicy. Can refill side dishes.
The tom yum soup and food are real spicy! Pandan chicken was small and didn't have pandan smell. Thai pineapple chicken rice was nice.
Finally tried the long queue Yong Tao Fu. Soup was sweet! Sauce was nice and the fried stuff were re-fried n hot, which made it nice. Depends on individual if the queue is worth the wait.

venue.name: Ang Mo Kio Central Market & Food Centre

tip.text: For salad, it was quite a big bowl. Wild mushroom soup was good. I like the mango mushroom wrap, with crunchy taste, mango taste and sauce used was tasty.
Crispy pork buns is a must! Ha Gao is nice; Siew Mai was normal. Nothing special for liver chee chong fan. Fu Pi Juan was nice.
Lemon cheesecake was refreshing and good! It's super sour if u intend to try the dried lemon slices on top of the cake...
Service was great! Food was served fast. Crispy squid was good. The squid ink mussel spaghetti was tasty. It looked spicy but it wasn't. Prawn linguine was tomato based filled with prawns.
Happy Valentine's Day! Red velvet waffle was good! Coffee almond icecream was bitter. Not sure why but the dark chocolate icecream was slightly bitter than usual.
The Pork mix toji teishoku was salty, recommended for pork lovers. Chawanmushi was special as it was a vegetable steamed egg. Saba shio teishoku's fish was fresh but be careful cos there r bones.
Cajun chicken burger and fries were good. Paying 50 cents for a small tub of cheese might not be recommended.
Tried the Mala & Pork Bone soup. Pork Bone soup was tasty! Crispy fish skin and Fried Beancurd skin were good! Service was good and attentive. U can mix ur own sauce or ask the staff to do so.

formattedAddress: #01-K1 TripleOne Somerset, 111 Somerset Rd (111 Somerset Rd)

venue.name: Imperial Treasure Windows of Hong Kong 御寶香港之窗

tip.text: Tried mango bingsu. Fresh mango n kiwi. But too ex for a dessert ($19.3). Nice ambience with lots of youngsters. Saw the owners too. Great location to attract pple.

The snow pear dessert was very sweet. The pink rose tangyuan was sweet with slight smell n taste of rose flowers. I expected peanut n black sesame each but gave me 4 black sesame. Tangyuan was not bad

formattedAddress: Jubilee Entertainment Hall (61 Ang Mo Kio Ave 8)

tip.text: Duck confit was dry. Ribeye was salty. Crab pasta can be made without chili but overall tasted dry. Chicken pasta was worthwhile but too much chicken. Mushroom soup was tasty.
Hup kee fried oyster omelette was good, crispy n full of oysters. Guan Kee grilled seafood's sambal stingray was not bad. Siti Khadijah seafood 's mutton satay was good. Craft beer not bad too...
Tried the 3 flavours Scallop, sweet corn n cheese. Cheese had a strong flavor out of the 3. Scallop was not bad but no scallop bits. Sweet corn was not too bad and with corns in it...
Tori paitan udon is chicken udon soup, safe choice. The pork udon had a special broth and pork was tasty. Fried crab meat was normal. Onigiri not bad.
Peking duck was nice, esp with plum sauce. Fish was fresh n noodles were tasty. The coconut dessert was special. The 薑湯湯圓 had a strong ginger taste, but with 2 dumplings only.
Pork chop is nice. Asked the chef to make it like the Hawaiian chik chop and it's delicious!
Hawaiian chicken chop was special becos of the pineapple n ham. Meat was not too bad. The fish in the fish n chips was good. Salsa is like a Thai salad which is spicy n sour. Good appetizer...

Asked for beehoon prawn but gave me yellow noodle with beehoon instead. There wasn't any pork ribs in my prawn noodle which I had to ask to change. But soup was nice and the Wu Xiang was hot n crispy.
The coconut toast was not bad.
Omelette was delicious! Duck like wanton was not bad but not filing. Full house on a weekday and have to make reservations. Outside seating is hot and may have mosquitoes...
Fried rice was fragrant and tasty. The dumpling was surprising nice, similar to Xiao Long Bao except little soup. 流沙包 tasted more like custard bun, not to my liking.
Happy Garden (幸福園）prawn noodle. Queued on a Sunday 1+pm and only left with normal prawn noodles. Like the soup base. Prawn was normal. After my lunch, everything was sold out...

venue.name: Ang Mo Kio Central Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Good place for gifts shopping! Bus 811 stops right in front of the building from Yishun mrt. Affordable fortune cats and Xmas trees!
Mango shaved ice is nice!!!!
Closing soon! Aunty Lee's last day will be on Saturday, 19th December...
Super long queue. But delivery was fast. No noodle, just plain soup. Takeaway is another queue. Good service fr Uncle who delivered even the takeover boxes to our table.

formattedAddress: #01-1084 People's Park Food Centre (32 New Market Rd.)

venue.name: Yong Xiang Xing Tou Fu 永祥兴豆腐

tip.text: Tried the chicken n pork bibimbap. Preferred the chicken one especially the crunchy taste. Sauce was spicy but had to add it to the rice to make it tastier.
Nice chill out place at a heartlands of Sembawang. Tried Thai Tea kaya, sweet n unique taste. Yuan yang drink was sweet. Honey lemongrass drink was gd for kids. Choco rainbow cake is popular cake.
Recommend the lobster spaghetti. Although there was no lobster meat, but the fragrance of the soup mix well with the spaghetti. Bread in French toast was soft but normal. Pancake chestnut was normal.
New Ebi Tamago... Nice! Prawn and Egg... But my love is still Yaki Mentako Miso
New mixed rice stall. Popular choice. Rojak not bad too.
Tried the special miso ramen. Meat was delicious. Thick ramen broth. Hot green tea comes in a pot.
Located near metro, the hotel is near main shopping area in Myeongdong. Love the amenities like steam iron, makeup booth, washing machine n dryer, computers, massage chairs and weighing scale!
Stylish bags can be found here. Usually there's discount available in the shops.
Cosy place to chill or relax. Good service from the staff. Took the effort to explain the different types of Korean teas. Cafe mocha was good. The "never catch a cold" tea is traditional bitter tea.
Lots of variety of food. Order at the cashier and wait for your number to be shown on the screen. Tried curry chicken and soft tofu soup.
Good and popular place for bbq meat. 8 kinds of meat which I like the curry and miso paste flavor. Love the vegetables. Service was fast n attentive but lack of manpower.
Good area for couple or families to ride bicycles together. Love the basketball courts. Can play badminton too. It's near KBS!
Chicken tenders was not bad despite being slightly dry. Chips and nachos were normal though. Real choco drink was bitter sweet. Hoegaarden was great with the chips!

venue.name: The Kind COFFEE & Tea with Book
The Kind COFFEE & Tea with Book
The Kind COFFEE & Tea with Book

tip.text: Food was good. Thai kway tiao tasted different but sweet. The seafood pasta was well decorated by cheese crust. Pumpkin appetizer was unique. U can get flowers there too. Nice ambience.
Love the dumplings! Outer skin was thin with lots of meat within. When dipped with sauce, gives a different flavor to the dumpling. Noodle soup was good as the noodles were so smooth.
Honey chicken was delicious! The outer skin was so crispy and tasty. It's located at 2nd floor, above KFC. Cannot mix n match (eg soy & honey) as only spicy & non-spicy can mix.
Cheap Korean products can be found here. It's like a paradise for cosmetics lovers.
It's a well known place for ginseng chicken. Choose the white chicken unless u like herbal (black chicken) taste. Salt n pepper can help with the herbal taste. Pancake was delicious!
Located at a deserted corner, this place is a must-stay if u wanna have a feel of traditional Korean life. No tv, shared toilet, simple life. The door lock spoilt n the owner changed it next day.
Their lunch set is popular but we tried dessert instead. Quite filling and too much shaved ice. Interesting ingredients which blended well together. Owner even gave us two free ice coffees!
This portion was half meal but too much for two. Soy chicken didn't had a strong taste and cheese fries were cold.
A place where you can try the morning breakfast of Koreans! Pork rice soup... Side dishes are cold and kimchi had a strong taste. You have to throw the rice into the soup.
Place full of colorful houses and steps. Get ready for a tour with lots of climbing of steps. Follow the fishes on the wall if u don't have a map. U can find a small house with love and locks.
Free flow of side dishes. Japchae was nice. Tried the mushroom "hang-over" soup. Unique which tasted as oats. Spicy pork rice was nice. Not much variety for non-spicy food lovers.
Minimum two types of meat. Side dishes can be refilled on your own. Meat can be burnt easily. Place the food by the side to keep hot but not cook them. Cut them into thin pieces before bbq...
Love the original doughnut! Mocha Caramel latte was pretty sweet.
You can't mix the type of meat so order one type per number of people/portion. They will cook for u n food pretty spicy (if u can't take spicy stuff). Overall food was not bad n affordable.
Love the dumpling! Skin was thin n delicious. 1st time tried cold noodle soup. Not bad of an experience but unknowingly, I tried to blow whenever I eat the noodles n then I realized, it's cold!
Tried the ginseng chicken porridge and abalone porridge. Porridge was not bad. The service was good. Quite crowded for a weekday morning.
All kinds of fish cakes! Not bad... You can pick one of everything. They will wrapped up in plastic and with sticks provided.
Worthwhile dinner place for 2. Food was alright and for non-spicy folks like me, Mild choice was bearable. Comes with fried rice or icecream at the end...
Ayam Penyet was crispy and meat was tender. Toufu was normal but curry was thick and good.
Interesting Injeolmi shave ice dessert. Almond, with soy bean powder, top with vanilla ice cream. Comes with condensed milk. Waited for 43mins. U will keep wondering if the device is faulty...
Belly Shiokouji was delicious. The Gokoku rice was not bad. Basil chicken salad was not bad either.
Duck confit was indeed good, crispy on the outside and tender on the inside. Salmon confit was not bad either. Both dishes were slightly salty. Reasonable price for a French restaurant.
The chicken parmigiana was bland and the skin was burnt. But the chicken lasagne was not bad, especially the cheese on top.
The teochew fish noodle / porridge stall @#01-35 is recommended. The fish is fresh and she will weigh every amt of fish to ensure correct amt of fish everytime. Soup was good too.

venue.name: Ang Mo Kio Central Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Nice ambience, even shot a couple taking wedding shots. Service was good n big breakfast was delicious, esp the pastries, toasted bread n scrambled eggs. Hot choco was more of a bitter taste.
Decent Thai food. Had the seafood phat thai n chicken rice with basil leaves. I can't take spicy well but when I asked for less spice in my Tom yum soup, it tasted like no spice at all.

location.state: สมุทรปราการ
formattedAddress: สมุทรปราการ 10540

venue.name: S&P (เอส แอนด์ พี)

tip.text: Waffle was soft with a cup of choco. Icecream was dark choco with brownie. Nice n cosy ambience too.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: Siam Square One (4th Fl, Winter Zone)
กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330

tip.text: Decent Thai food. The fried rice with fish n salted egg was unique n good. Loved the crunchy taste. Green curry wasn't that spicy.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330

venue.name: White Flower Factory (ครัวดอกไม้ขาว)

tip.text: It's all about Mango! Sticky rice was small so it wouldn't be too filling. Icecream was like mango sorbet. Pudding was not bad. Readily cut mango was sweet.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: 5/48(A), 5/49 Siam Square Soi 5 (near Novotel Bangkok Hotel)
กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330

venue.name: MangoTango (แมงโก้แทงโก้)

tip.text: Eggs benedict was normal, but the bread wasn't to my liking. Crabmeat aglio olio was good. Caramel pork shop was unique. Choco peanut butter lava cake-sinfully good!

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10110

venue.name: Chu Chocolate Bar & Café (ชู ช็อคโกแล็ต บาร์ & คาเฟ่)

tip.text: Service wasn't good. Food was normal with live music. Ordered crabs which was not worthwhile cos the pincers meat were tiny n little. Pineapple fried rice portion wasn't that much either.

location.city: อำเภอหัวหิน
location.state: จังหวัดประจวบคีรีขันธ์

จังหวัดประจวบคีรีขันธ์

venue.name: Sailom Restaurant (ห้องอาหารสายลม)

tip.text: Sushi was ok, riceball with special urchin sauce was pretty filling. But the sauce wasn't enough. Yaki onigiri was quite burnt. Tori soba was not bad. Love the Hirayachi. Lights will dim near end day.

contact.facebookName: Mekiki no ginji in BKK k-village

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10110

venue.name: Mekiki no Ginji (Mekiki no Ginji (目利きの銀次))

tip.text: Buffet serves decent Korean food but due to open area, the food gets cold easily. The main course quantity were small portions too.
雙魚麵線 isn't tasty, same goes for the soup. Surprisingly fried fish was okay.

venue.name: Ang Mo Kio Central Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Love the ramen here. But miso soup base wasn't to my liking. This is what was left of my regular butter corn miso ramen.

formattedAddress: Takashimaya B2, Ngee Ann City (391A Orchard Rd)

tip.text: Cheesy chicken rice was not bad, especially the cheesy egg. Comes with own sauce. Seasonal (Tomato) soup was okay too. Caramel icecream was good.

formattedAddress: #01-34, AMK Hub (53 Ang Mo Kio Ave 3)

tip.text: Love this Yin yang mango black glutinous rice! Although it's abit sweet...
潮州魚丸(beside Pontian) fishball noodles wasn't nice. Told them twice w/o vinegar but in the end still added in n had to ask to redo on the spot.

venue.name: Ang Mo Kio Central Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Good place for friends gatherings. Big portion food but chicken was normal.
Food was normal, ambience was good, not crowded. Service was good too.
Good jap food! Love the origiri! Not available at some outlets such as AMK hub.
Similar to Astons@Centrepoint with a salad bar. Although the chicken or dory fish portions were small, but with the free flow food at salad bar, you will certainly eat at will.
Value for money. Mixed grill n escargot were good. Chicken was more tender than pork. Aglio olio was normal. Dory fish was good but breaded prawns was normal too.
Weirdest thing to happen is when they ran out of fries and the substitute would only be rice. U dun have a choice. Hope they have more fries in future.
The waffles r gd. Marconi n cheese pretty cheesy but not that tasty. Service was quite slow. They serve certain food at different times. Like pizza to be served after 3pm. But overall it's good!
Decent Thai food but have to queue. Staff were polite. Phai Thai wasn't that sweet and clear tomyum seafood wasn't very spicy. Fav would be the banana leaves chicken n the banana leaves were crispy!
Bfast bread is pretty big, unlike the shop beside. But French toast wasn't nice...

Chee chong fan was good with unique sauce. Fried tofu stick was normal with too much salad sauce. Tomyam siewmai tasted like otah. 腐皮捲 was so crispy! Fried banana-sweet and salty. Chaisiew bao not bad
Love the soft shell crab! Phai Thai wasn't that flavory as Thai Express. But it was good too!
Love the fries! Belgium beer was good!
Hawaii pizza was oven-baked, juicy n pretty big for one. Seafood aglio olio was unlike usual spicy aglio olio that we ate b4. Strong rum taste for the tiramisu which was good!

formattedAddress: #01-12/14/15, 2450 Ang Mo Kio Ave 8 (Ang Mo Kio Ave 3)

venue.name: Ya Kun Kaya Toast 亞坤

tip.text: Love the crispy bun with condensed milk @ Tsui Wah!

contact.facebookName: Hong Kong International Airport 香港國際機場

venue.name: Hong Kong International Airport (HKG) (香港國際機場)

tip.text: Food was not bad! Plentiful seafood ingredients in the seafood pasta.
Check out the pizzas from Rorbua Pub. They are good!
Love this place. Walking distance to the main town area with restaurants all nearby. Make your own waffles n u may be able to catch some dinner if u r going for the northern lights exploration.
BBQ pork belly with honey sauce is nice. Love the prawn in beancurd skin fritters & crispy BBQ honey pork bun!

formattedAddress: #B2-01/02, AMK Hub (53 Ang Mo Kio Ave 3)

tip.text: Despite many recommendations, still felt that it's not worth waiting for 1 hour. Not for pple who likes strong flavor food.

venue.name: Huat Kee Kway Chap 發記馃汁

tip.text: Like the Yaki Ebi & Yaki Crab Gyoza! They suit my tastes because they are of strong flavor.
The French toast is not bad, but not that tasty as I have eaten elsewhere. The eggs were more orangey than usual.
Crispy noodle is good. Love the xiao long bao. The wantons were fresh too.

venue.name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao 翡翠拉麵小籠包

tip.text: Like the hazelnut choco spin! They don't serve whipped cream, yeah!
Millionaire salad was normal but no lettuce in it. Chicken Schmitzel was good n the breaded skin wasn't thick. But the sauce tasted like melted butter, sinful! Spike D is for durian n choco lovers!
Love the magic beans!!!
大家來 Chicken rice was not bad but doesn't justify the long queue (if any). But we loved the Chwee Kway!

formattedAddress: Blk 628 Ang Mo Kio Ave 4 (Ang Mo Kio St 61)

venue.name: 628 Ang Mo Kio Market & Food Centre

tip.text: All dimsum is small in portion n caters for 3. Liu sa bao was small n skin was abit thick. But still not bad. Like the red bean banana, carrot cake, beancurd prawn roll. The rest was decent n normal.

venue.name: Yi Dian Xin Hong Kong Dim Sum 一点心港式点心

tip.text: Love the waffles! Choco truffle Icecream was quite sweet. Tried the rootbeer cake -> Choco cake with a taste of rootbeer n vanilla Icecream. But no ice water being served. In need of it after that.
Teh halia n lime juice quite sweet. Egg n bom pratas aren't that fanastic. What's nice is probably the curry, which is also sweet.

formattedAddress: 490 Toa Payoh Lor 6  #01-15 (Toa Payoh HDB Hub)

tip.text: The pasta was abit hard when chewed and the seafood wasn't as fresh as what I expected. But the tiramisu is a must-try and their service was good! Enjoyable dinner despite the food...

formattedAddress: Basement, Grand Hyatt Hotel (10 Scotts Rd)

tip.text: Love the magic beans 魔豆
Love the Tori Karage & Garlic Rice!
A place with no signboard but a little name "Dept of Caffeine". Recommended->Cafe Mocha, Buttermilk waffles with bananas! Waffles aren't those usual thick waffles, delicious with Icecream n bananas!
Just love the polo with yuan yang milk tea. Must buy and certainly worth the queue!
The salty beancurd was certainly a special flavor, but after eating near half bowl, feel sick abt the taste. The only thing that was not bad, shld be the egg crepe. To me, it's over-rated.

formattedAddress: 忠孝東路一段108號2F (紹興南街)

venue.name: Fu Hang Dou Jiang (阜杭豆漿)

tip.text: The banana pancakes was sweet n nice, seemed like eating banana cake though. Truffle fries was not bad but not the best that I have tried.
Steam bread with butter kaya.. Shiok to eat while it's hot!!!

venue.name: Ya Kun Kaya Toast 亞坤
Ya Kun Kaya Toast 亞坤

tip.text: The 成美 porridge not bad... Will eat this stall whenever feel like eating porridge. Even good for toddlers but need to mention to them not to add anything since it's for kids...

venue.name: Ang Mo Kio Central Market & Food Centre

tip.text: Attracted by the smell of its waffle, tried Bananas about Nutella & Horlicks icecream. Waffle was small but was so-so. The ice cream flavors that we chose was normal too. Nice ambience though...

formattedAddress: The Central #02-79/90 (6 Eu Tong Sen St)

tip.text: The toast was crispy but yet soft. In general, the big breakfast was good. The spaghetti prawn aglio olio was nice! Although the serving bowl was small, the portion was sufficient.
Carupano Venezuela is real super chocolatey, get it unless u are a fan of thick choco. Guanaja chocolate soufflé isn't that sweet; Make a hole to pour in the vanilla sauce. But I like the sherbet!

formattedAddress: #01-11, The Pier @ Robertson (80 Mohamed Sultan Rd.)

tip.text: Waffles was soft and durian Icecream had a surprising strong durian taste. Though chocolate durian was normal, but I felt it was nice. Take the normal waffle, more worthwhile

formattedAddress: #01-74, The Central (6 Eu Tong Sen Street)

tip.text: Love the food, ambience and service. Squid ink pasta needs to be pre-ordered and I love it! Risotto seafood was one of the best we had in sg. Choco rum & raisin cake was sweet n chocolatey!
Love the chocolate ice cream, especially waffles! Nicer than Udders. Shiok!
Durian mousse standard has certainly dropped. Even had tiny ice cubes inside the mousse.
